            <div class="bts">
                <center><h1>Know The Basics :</h1><center>
                <h2>what is FrontEnd?</h2>
                <p>
                    Front end development in web development refers to the part of a website or web application that users interact with directly. It encompasses the design, layout, and interactivity of a site, focusing on creating a visually appealing and intuitive user experience. Front end developers use a combination of languages such as HTML, CSS, and JavaScript to build the structure, style, and functionality of web pages. HTML provides the basic structure of a page, CSS is used for styling and layout, and JavaScript adds interactivity and dynamic features. Additionally, front end developers often utilize frameworks and libraries like React, Angular, or Vue.js to streamline development and enhance user interfaces. The goal of front end development is to create responsive, accessible, and engaging web experiences that effectively communicate information and facilitate user interaction.</p>
                <h2>what is BackEnd?</h2>
                <p>Backend development in web development refers to the server-side of a website or web application. It involves managing data, processing requests, and ensuring the smooth functioning of the application's logic. Backend developers use programming languages like Python, Ruby, Java, PHP, or Node.js, along with frameworks like Django, Ruby on Rails, Spring Boot, Laravel, or Express.js to handle these tasks efficiently. They are responsible for implementing security measures, managing user authentication, and ensuring overall performance and scalability.</p>
                <h2>what is DataBase?</h2>
                <p>
                    Database development involves managing data within a web application. Developers work with systems like MySQL, PostgreSQL, or MongoDB to design schemas, create tables, and optimize queries. They ensure data integrity and collaborate with backend developers to integrate database functionality seamlessly.</p>
